# Layout Isolation

Read `docs/Layout_Isolation_Rules.md` before changing layouts, shells, or global CSS.

## Each area owns its layout

Dashboard · Studio · Reader · Character pages · Admin · Authentication — each has a root wrapper and scoped CSS imported only from that area’s entry component.

| Area | Root | CSS import location |
|------|------|---------------------|
| Dashboard | `.charid-dashboard-shell` | `DashboardShell.tsx` |
| Studio | `.charid-editor-root` | `ComicPageEditorView.tsx` |
| Marketing | `.charid-marketing-shell` | `src/app/page.tsx` |
| Auth | `.charid-auth-shell` | login/signup pages |

## Scoping

- **Studio** rules only beneath `.charid-editor-root` (`@scope` in `charid-editor-layout.css`)
- **Dashboard** rules only beneath `.charid-dashboard-shell`
- **Reader** rules only beneath `.charid-reader-shell` (when added)

## Never

- Import area layout CSS from `globals.css`
- Unscoped selectors that reposition layouts (`.shell`, `.sidebar`, `* { padding: 0 }` at document root)
- Modify shared layout components for Studio-specific fixes — create Studio-specific components instead
- Modify `DashboardShell` to solve Studio problems

## globals.css

Design tokens and non-layout utilities only. No Studio grid, sidebar, or shell positioning rules without `.charid-editor-root` prefix.

See also `docs/Studio_Shell_Rules.md` for frozen Studio shell grid/DOM (extend inside shell, do not redesign).
